We can create a device file in two ways.

Manually
Automaticall

provide a convenient way to access system resources without requiring the application programmer to know how the underlying device works

they are in /dev dir

manually >>>> mknod -m <perm> <name> <device type> <maj> <min>
created and registered with a major number and a minor number.

Dyn: using udev

three steps 
Include the header file linux/device.h and linux/kdev_t.h
Create the struct Class
Create Device with the class which is created by the above step




